-- Day 18: Total Drug Sales per Manufacturer (Formatted in Millions)
-- Source: DataLemur (CVS Health SQL Interview)

-- Problem:
-- Calculate the total drug sales for each manufacturer.
-- Round the total sales to the nearest million and format as "$X million".
-- Sort results in descending order of total sales.
-- In case of ties, sort alphabetically by manufacturer name.

-- Table Schema:
-- pharmacy_sales(product_id, units_sold, total_sales, cogs, manufacturer, drug)

-- Approach:
-- 1. Group data by manufacturer (one row per manufacturer)
-- 2. Calculate total sales using SUM(total_sales)
-- 3. Convert total sales to millions by dividing by 1,000,000
-- 4. Round to the nearest million using ROUND()
-- 5. Format output as "$X million" using string concatenation
-- 6. Sort by actual total sales (not rounded value) in descending order
-- 7. Break ties using manufacturer name in ascending order

-- Concepts Used:
-- GROUP BY, SUM(), ROUND(), String Concatenation, ORDER BY

SELECT
  manufacturer,
  '$' || ROUND(SUM(total_sales) / 1000000.0) || ' million' AS sales_mil
FROM pharmacy_sales
GROUP BY manufacturer
ORDER BY SUM(total_sales) DESC, manufacturer;
